WEBVTT

01:17.058 --> 01:18.180
Good morning, Concord.

01:19.542 --> 01:23.508
My name is Jay Burkett, and I'm a member of the pulpit ministry team.

01:23.528 --> 01:32.321
And one of the responsibilities of the pulpit ministry team is to fill the pulpit every Sunday, because it's really important to have a preacher during the preaching time.

01:33.824 --> 01:42.237
It took us three meetings to finally come to that consensus, and the guys talked about it, and Bonnie Stephanie all have her stood up and said, look, we've got to have a preacher during the preaching time, guys.

01:42.277 --> 01:43.218
What are we talking about?

01:43.714 --> 01:45.357
So that's one of our responsibilities.

01:45.537 --> 02:03.090
And we are so blessed here at Concord because for the past eight weeks, this really is an indication of the strength of our congregation, the strength of our staff, just the strength of the body here at Concord because for the past eight weeks, we have been able to fill the pulpit with a member of our congregation in JoJo Thomas.

02:03.490 --> 02:10.738
And two guys on staff, Jamie Smith and Brandon Roney, and they did not just feel the pulpit, but they did an outstanding job feeling the pulpit.

02:10.758 --> 02:14.202
So just join me in thanking them and their willingness to do that.

02:15.123 --> 02:16.304
They did a great job.

02:16.945 --> 02:26.415
But with them feeling the pulpit, what that enabled us to do as a team is to focus all of our attention and efforts in trying to find and identify an interim senior pastor.

02:26.435 --> 02:32.722
And so during that search, the Lord has led us to a man to consider for that that we would like to put before you to consider.

02:32.994 --> 02:34.436
And he is here this morning.

02:34.456 --> 02:36.278
We invited him to come and to fill the pulpit.

02:36.298 --> 02:37.739
We're very, very excited about it.

02:38.260 --> 02:42.004
And he'll do a little bit more of an introduction as to kind of who he is and what his background is.

02:42.044 --> 02:45.768
So just join me in welcoming and let me introduce to you, Derek Spain.

02:46.388 --> 02:46.789
Come on, Derek.

02:49.291 --> 02:50.713
Thank you, Jay.

02:50.733 --> 02:51.073
Thank you, man.

02:52.194 --> 02:53.556
I am glad to be here.

02:53.796 --> 02:59.282
Boy, God has been doing a great work at Concord for a lot of years and excited to be here today.

02:59.714 --> 03:04.944
Some of the people who are connected Concord, you may know of a guy named Levi.

03:05.525 --> 03:09.673
He and I went to seminary together a few years ago, and so known him for many years.

03:09.933 --> 03:21.234
And then also, some of you have been here for Concord for a while, you may know the name of Steve Parr, and Steve is a guy that I've known for many, many years.

03:21.346 --> 03:26.815
first brought me on staff at Hebering Church in Dacula as a student pastor a long time ago.

03:27.777 --> 03:33.226
So I want to tell you a little bit about my family and a little bit about where God's had us through the years.

03:33.246 --> 03:40.819
I want to welcome, though, all of the people of Concord, not just here on this campus, but on all the campuses and even streaming online.

03:41.140 --> 03:44.786
I'm glad you've joined us because a Concord God is doing a great work.

03:45.378 --> 03:47.561
Our family, Kim, and I have been married this week.

03:47.581 --> 03:50.845
We celebrated 25 years of being married, so we're excited about that.

03:51.046 --> 03:52.027
Yeah, it's a big deal.

03:53.369 --> 03:54.490
We have three children.

03:55.692 --> 03:56.934
Our oldest is in college.

03:57.875 --> 03:59.878
We have two boys and a girl, so our oldest in college.

03:59.958 --> 04:06.807
Our other son is just graduated from high school, and our daughter is about to be a sophomore at the Hula High School, so those are our kids.

04:07.508 --> 04:11.954
As I said, I started as a student pastor at Hebrew, and I'm actually

04:12.450 --> 04:17.378
and graduate of D'Cula High School many years ago, graduating group in that community.

04:18.039 --> 04:19.521
Steve Parr, that's how I first knew him.

04:19.541 --> 04:28.415
My dad was his baseball coach when he was in high school, so Steve remembers me when I was this big, chasing all his foul balls when he was trying to hit home runs.

04:28.896 --> 04:38.130
But, I grew up and graduate of D'Cula High School also attended and met my wife at Shorter College, now Shorter University, and so that's where we met.

04:38.242 --> 04:43.328
And then I was a student pastor here for 10 years, and then the Lord called us to the mountains of New York.

04:43.388 --> 04:48.594
So after I actually went to seminary here in Atlanta, New Orleans seminary, but here in the Atlanta campus.

04:49.255 --> 04:52.018
And then the Lord called us to the mountains of New York.

04:52.058 --> 04:53.580
And we served there for 10 years.

04:54.201 --> 04:57.245
I was the lead pastor of a church, Lake Placid Baptist Church.

04:57.925 --> 04:58.626
His name is the church.

04:59.047 --> 05:05.234
And then also I spent about half my time doing ministry with winter, sports,

05:05.314 --> 05:12.744
athletes trying to get the gospel to bob sledters and ski jumpers and figure skaters and all these kind of people.

05:12.784 --> 05:17.912
So it was a really exciting different kind of ministry and God worked in some amazing ways.

05:18.472 --> 05:31.090
While we were in New York, our church grew and God also gave us the opportunity to plant a church about an hour away from us and then about 30 minutes away we had begun to plant another church when the Lord called us back to Georgia.

05:31.234 --> 05:35.638
That church, that second one is now going, and it's strong, and so we praise God for that.

05:36.479 --> 05:50.112
As I said, when we moved back, we loved New York, but we're from Georgia, and our kids, we only had two when we moved to New York, and we came back with three, right?

05:50.172 --> 05:56.518
So we brought one and found one up there, and anyway, however that happened.

05:56.538 --> 06:01.042
So we like to say it this way, because my wife, she's from Cobb County,

06:01.154 --> 06:07.725
And we like to say we were two southerners who moved back home, but we brought three Yankees with us.

06:08.726 --> 06:14.476
And so our kids had to actually go to the adjustment of, because they grew up in New York, and all they knew was New York.

06:14.536 --> 06:16.559
And so they made the adjustment moving back here.

06:17.000 --> 06:23.410
So for the last seven years or so, I had the opportunity to serve as the executive pastor of a Hebran church in Dicula.

06:23.490 --> 06:25.272
And grateful to God for that.

06:25.632 --> 06:31.678
And one of my roles as the number two guy there was to help the church because we went through an interim period.

06:32.059 --> 06:36.163
And so from Pastor Kevin to Pastor Landon was actually 14 months.

06:36.483 --> 06:41.908
And so my job was to help lead the staff during that transition and to lead the church during that transition.

06:42.269 --> 06:43.790
And so grateful to God for that.

06:44.111 --> 06:51.538
I'm really excited to be here this morning and we'll see what God has in the future and excited for Concord and exciting time.

06:51.650 --> 06:57.379
And it's exciting every time, I'll say it this way, every time we get to interact with God's Word.

06:57.819 --> 07:04.029
And so I hope you come on Sundays expecting to hear from God, but not just to hear, but also to obey.

07:04.569 --> 07:10.278
Could I ask you to take your Bible and open to Matthew chapter nine and verse 35?

07:10.759 --> 07:15.926
This morning I want us to talk about being on mission everywhere.

07:15.946 --> 07:21.074
I know Concord, we talk about making disciples

07:21.186 --> 07:30.095
Everywhere, part of that making disciples is realizing that everywhere we go, we are on mission with God and on mission for God.

07:30.115 --> 07:41.806
I want us to look at these few verses in Matthew's Gospel this morning to see how Jesus went about his ministry and see how God can teach us from that.

07:42.247 --> 07:45.590
And again, that we would hear and obey what God's cause to do.

07:45.610 --> 07:47.852
Would you please stand with me for the reading of God's word?

07:48.433 --> 07:49.714
Matthew chapter nine,

07:49.986 --> 07:51.007
beginning in verse 35.

07:52.610 --> 08:04.506
The Bible says this, Jesus continued going around to all the towns and villages, teaching in their synagogues, preaching the good news of the kingdom, and healing every disease and every sickness.

08:05.347 --> 08:14.259
And when he saw the crowds, he felt compassion for them because they were distressed and dejected, like sheep without a shepherd.

08:14.980 --> 08:19.346
And then he said to his disciples, the harvest is abundant, but the workers are few.

08:19.810 --> 08:25.619
Therefore pray to the Lord of the harvest to send out workers into his harvest.

08:25.899 --> 08:26.620
Let's pray together.

08:27.802 --> 08:30.466
Jesus, we thank you for your word.

08:31.027 --> 08:33.811
We thank you for your Holy Spirit who is here in our midst.

08:34.532 --> 08:38.258
And as we gather, we ask that Lord, our focus will be on you.

08:39.159 --> 08:46.650
If either through your word, would you speak to us today that we would not just be here as of the word, but we would do what it says.

08:47.452 --> 08:49.074
Through the power of your spirit,

08:49.346 --> 08:56.434
in obedience to your word, as youth change our lives, may we live differently in this world.

08:56.875 --> 08:58.997
It's in Jesus' name we pray, amen.

09:01.360 --> 09:06.466
Matthew chapter nine, verse 35, is a summary of Jesus' early ministry.

09:07.427 --> 09:11.312
And it shows us how he was on mission everywhere that he went.

09:11.792 --> 09:14.916
And I wanna show you three big things today from this passage.

09:14.936 --> 09:16.498
And I'll get right to number one.

09:16.674 --> 09:20.599
The first one is this, I want us to see the crowds.

09:21.541 --> 09:28.731
If we're going to be on mission everywhere, we have to see the crowds of people all around us.

09:29.151 --> 09:37.523
It says in verse 36, when he saw the crowds, he felt compassion for them.

09:37.543 --> 09:38.244
He did something.

09:38.784 --> 09:42.389
It began though, before he did anything, he saw them.

09:42.990 --> 09:45.874
He saw the crowds of people.

09:47.234 --> 09:49.518
So let me ask you the question in your life.

09:50.138 --> 09:54.806
Who are the crowds of people that you see every day?

09:55.767 --> 09:57.670
Who are the crowds of people that you see every day?

09:57.890 --> 10:07.125
If you're a student, teenagers, if you're a student, I'd be at school, but I mean, you're so excited, maybe in school, excited to get back at it.

10:07.145 --> 10:15.698
But one of the things you have people around you every single day, all these crowds of people, other students, teachers, coaches,

10:15.938 --> 10:19.102
All the faculty and staff, you have people around you every day.

10:20.124 --> 10:21.966
Who are the crowns of people you see every day?

10:22.086 --> 10:27.474
You know, when we're in our homes and in our neighborhoods, all of us, there's people around us all the time.

10:28.275 --> 10:34.163
People around us, people that we know, if we live on a road and men, there's our neighbors.

10:34.203 --> 10:37.127
They may be five miles away, maybe right next door.

10:37.367 --> 10:41.112
We have people around us, we go to the grocery store, we go to shopping, everywhere that we go.

10:41.152 --> 10:45.458
Adults, we go to our office, we're in our business, people in and out,

10:45.602 --> 10:49.107
of our lives every day, people in and out of the business, we're going different places.

10:49.488 --> 10:51.611
In other words, guys, here's the bottom line.

10:51.711 --> 10:53.934
Just like Jesus, there's people around us.

10:54.595 --> 10:55.176
We got to see them.

10:55.196 --> 11:01.925
Who are the crowds of people that we see and that you see every single day?

11:03.067 --> 11:09.276
If we're going to be on mission everywhere, we have to realize that these crowds of people, we have to see them like Jesus' song.

11:10.057 --> 11:13.842
And like Jesus, notice the individuals

11:14.178 --> 11:15.400
in the crowds.

11:16.862 --> 11:20.548
You know, if you go to a football game, you're in a big stadium with lots of people.

11:21.749 --> 11:27.799
There's crowd roaring, there's all these people, but these are individuals who are there.

11:28.440 --> 11:35.530
And so spiritually speaking, if we're gonna see people the way Jesus did, we're gonna see the individuals all around us.

11:35.831 --> 11:43.282
If you look at chapters eight and nine of Matthew's Gospel just quickly, you see that Jesus cleansed a man

11:43.522 --> 11:44.343
who had leprosy.

11:44.543 --> 11:47.387
These are how the headings in your Bible are helpful, by the way.

11:47.848 --> 11:49.510
He cleansed the man with leprosy.

11:50.151 --> 11:52.013
He saw the centurion's faith.

11:52.674 --> 11:54.697
Jesus healed people at Capernaum.

11:55.758 --> 11:59.383
Jesus with his disciples was on a boat and the winds and the waves obeyed him.

11:59.903 --> 12:07.954
Jesus drives out demons that were afflicting people and gattering person in particular, too.

12:08.034 --> 12:12.059
The son of man, he healed and forgives people, begin in chapter nine.

12:12.439 --> 12:17.446
He calls Matthew to be one of his followers, to be one of his disciples, one of his learners.

12:17.926 --> 12:20.309
He answers questions about fasting.

12:20.610 --> 12:21.511
He takes time for that.

12:21.851 --> 12:27.518
He restores a girl's life and he heals a woman who had been afflicted.

12:27.718 --> 12:29.240
He heals a blind man.

12:29.481 --> 12:30.642
He drives out demons.

12:30.882 --> 12:32.004
What is the point of all this?

12:33.225 --> 12:37.170
These are personal encounters people have with Jesus.

12:37.890 --> 12:40.894
And so with each of us, we ask the question, who are the people that I see every day?

12:41.395 --> 12:42.777
Let me give you an example.

12:42.797 --> 12:50.767
When we were in New York doing ministry with winter sports athletes, one of the groups of people that was there were bobsledters.

12:51.168 --> 12:53.411
Some of you know this sport of bobsled.

12:53.771 --> 13:01.382
It's like a mile long water slide, but it's frozen, so it's a mile long ice chute.

13:01.402 --> 13:07.730
And you get in this machine that holds either two or four people, weighing hundreds of pounds,

13:08.290 --> 13:12.075
And you drive this thing about 95 miles an hour.

13:12.676 --> 13:16.120
It does have a break, but you don't break it until the very end.

13:16.220 --> 13:20.766
Because if you break, and it just grabs the ice, if you break it on the way down, you're going to crash.

13:21.147 --> 13:25.833
So the break is like, just at the very end, so you don't flop the track, they break it so they can stop.

13:26.093 --> 13:27.174
That's the true story.

13:27.194 --> 13:28.276
Okay.

13:28.296 --> 13:31.039
So you go in on this thing, I mean, just fearlessly.

13:31.520 --> 13:36.306
Well, one of the guys that was a driver for the U.S. Bobsler team that we met

13:36.450 --> 13:38.373
pretty early on in our time there.

13:38.473 --> 13:39.254
His name was John.

13:39.314 --> 13:41.857
He was one of the youngest drivers in the US bobsled team.

13:41.877 --> 13:43.159
He was just a teenager at the time.

13:44.281 --> 13:45.362
This guy, Daredevil.

13:45.562 --> 13:47.605
Like all bobsled drivers, Daredevil.

13:47.645 --> 13:49.628
Anything you could think of Daredevil, he would try.

13:49.648 --> 13:52.592
I mean, today he's all into scuba diving and stuff like that.

13:52.632 --> 13:55.095
He's always had a fast motorcycle.

13:55.115 --> 13:55.636
You just get it.

13:55.656 --> 13:56.798
I mean, he's just that kind of a guy.

13:57.639 --> 13:58.900
So, John was a bobsled driver.

13:58.920 --> 14:05.970
I've been driving since he was like probably under 10 years old because his parents were both in the sport back in the day.

14:06.594 --> 14:13.406
I met his parents before I met him because we would volunteer and serve at this race, races, and got to know them.

14:13.446 --> 14:15.429
And then they pointed out how this is my son, John.

14:16.071 --> 14:18.254
Well, fast forward a little bit in time.

14:18.775 --> 14:20.979
John's father came down with cancer.

14:21.801 --> 14:24.005
It was stage four lung cancer.

14:24.726 --> 14:26.349
And I heard that he was in the hospital.

14:26.389 --> 14:31.698
And so I drove, like many of you would, two hours, right, drove to the hospital to visit his family.

14:32.290 --> 14:35.034
So stalled John and his mom and his dad there in the hospital.

14:35.054 --> 14:37.077
We had some prayer together and left.

14:37.598 --> 14:40.422
A few weeks later, John's dad passed away.

14:41.143 --> 14:41.824
It's really sad.

14:42.505 --> 14:43.146
Dad passed away.

14:43.206 --> 14:50.917
So again, got in the car, drove down to the funeral, was there with coaches and athletes and they were all there to support their friend John.

14:52.960 --> 14:59.890
A few weeks later, I was walking in and about to start a Bible study that we had at the Olympic Training Center.

15:00.514 --> 15:03.838
And I saw John, I said, John, hey, man, you will come to Bible study.

15:03.858 --> 15:04.539
Well, he came.

15:05.800 --> 15:07.903
And he told me later, much later.

15:08.303 --> 15:13.009
He said, Derek, the reason I came was you had been nice to my family and me.

15:14.571 --> 15:17.094
And so I thought I would come, at least to pay you back.

15:18.516 --> 15:19.858
He says, the crazy thing happened.

15:20.178 --> 15:22.921
I sat down in the Bible study and it wasn't boring.

15:24.904 --> 15:27.106
That's like an indictment on our Bible studies, right?

15:27.807 --> 15:30.130
He expected it to be boring, but it wasn't.

15:30.882 --> 15:46.724
He got to hear athletes share their testimonies and for us to interact with God's word, guys within a few weeks, John had come to faith in Jesus Christ and his life was gloriously saved.

15:47.586 --> 15:50.590
I'll be able to tell you in future weeks more about his story.

15:50.890 --> 15:51.791
It's pretty amazing.

15:52.252 --> 15:59.282
But the bottom line was not only me, but other believers had seen John.

16:00.258 --> 16:03.162
And they saw that he was a person in need of God's love.

16:03.182 --> 16:04.343
He needed hope.

16:04.363 --> 16:14.135
How many of the people that you see every day, if you're going to see people, if you're going to notice the individuals in the crowd, do you think about does this person even know Jesus?

16:14.976 --> 16:16.558
Where are they going to spend eternity?

16:16.838 --> 16:19.622
We have to begin with noticing the individuals in the crowd.

16:19.842 --> 16:26.450
So I would ask you, students, you might to school on your end class, how many of my friends know Jesus?

16:26.690 --> 16:32.437
Folks, everywhere that we go, in our homes, our neighborhoods, our community, to the people we know, notice the individuals in the crowd.

16:32.457 --> 16:36.422
So it begins, if we're gonna be on mission everywhere, we need to say, God, open my eyes.

16:37.303 --> 16:43.591
That would see people the way Jesus saw them, the individuals in the crowds who need God's love.

16:43.611 --> 16:47.496
Number two is this, not only see the crowds, number two, I want you to feel the compassion.

16:48.537 --> 16:55.986
It says in verse 35, Jesus continued going around all the towns and villages, teaching in there,

16:56.162 --> 17:00.849
synagogues preaching the good news of the kingdom, healing every disease and sickness.

17:01.570 --> 17:10.324
When he saw the crowds, he felt compassion for them because they were distressed and dejected like sheep without a shepherd.

17:11.446 --> 17:16.414
This word compassion literally means from the gut.

17:17.716 --> 17:20.360
It was something that wasn't just like, I feel bad for them.

17:21.221 --> 17:22.463
It bothered him.

17:22.764 --> 17:24.306
Have you ever had that happen to you?

17:24.642 --> 17:28.507
That I mean, you see something going on and it just like bothers you.

17:28.607 --> 17:30.390
It just grips you in your gut.

17:30.930 --> 17:32.753
That's the way Jesus was.

17:33.554 --> 17:35.837
This compassion that he felt for them.

17:36.238 --> 17:36.558
Why?

17:36.979 --> 17:47.713
The Bible tells us they were distressed and dejected or other translations in English say they were weary and worn out, weary and scattered.

17:48.014 --> 17:50.837
They were broken and they were battered.

17:51.338 --> 17:54.322
They were just, I mean worn out

17:54.402 --> 17:56.204
They were helpless and hopeless.

17:56.965 --> 18:01.250
The people here were so helpless and hopeless.

18:01.811 --> 18:04.874
And yet there's an interesting phrase in here in verse 36.

18:05.074 --> 18:08.819
It says they were like sheep without a shepherd.

18:09.820 --> 18:10.440
Now think about this.

18:11.962 --> 18:14.585
The Bible talks about God being our great shepherd, right?

18:14.665 --> 18:22.194
But spiritual leaders today pass the churches and in Jesus' day, the leaders of Israel

18:22.466 --> 18:25.551
they were called to be the shepherds of the people of Israel.

18:26.132 --> 18:28.816
So I have a question for you.

18:28.836 --> 18:30.358
This is like you're gonna have to raise your hand a second.

18:30.378 --> 18:31.059
All right, you gotta pick.

18:32.361 --> 18:38.190
How many of you think that the people of Israel had shepherds when Jesus was there?

18:38.210 --> 18:39.692
Because it says they were sheep without a shepherd.

18:40.013 --> 18:41.475
Raise your hand if you think they had shepherds.

18:42.296 --> 18:43.037
Okay, put your hands down.

18:43.358 --> 18:44.920
Raise your hand if you think they didn't have shepherds.

18:45.781 --> 18:46.643
Okay, put your hands down.

18:46.663 --> 18:47.424
Raise your hand if you wish.

18:47.985 --> 18:48.726
Derek, just tell us.

18:48.766 --> 18:49.768
Do they have shepherds or not?

18:50.248 --> 18:51.410
Okay, yeah, just tell us.

18:51.810 --> 19:00.283
They had shepherds, but the problem was the shepherds weren't shepherding.

19:00.303 --> 19:07.614
And so many people that we know, they may even claim something spiritual.

19:08.575 --> 19:13.803
They may even attend a church somewhere, but the question is do they really know Jesus?

19:15.005 --> 19:20.914
These people, Jesus saw he had compassion on them

19:20.994 --> 19:27.503
from the gut and like him, compassion for us needs to lead to action.

19:28.124 --> 19:31.328
Compassion leads to action.

19:31.989 --> 19:35.874
Let me show you what Jesus did, verse 35, it says three things.

19:36.174 --> 19:37.076
Can you name a form?

19:37.196 --> 19:39.619
Jesus did this and this and this.

19:39.699 --> 19:40.260
What did he do?

19:40.360 --> 19:45.246
He taught, he preached and he healed.

19:45.907 --> 19:47.890
Yeah, he taught, he preached, he healed.

19:48.418 --> 19:51.523
You know, the Bible talks about giving a cup of cold water in Jesus' name.

19:52.444 --> 20:00.597
We talk about things that are ministries like giving food to people who are hungry, giving clothes to people who need clothing.

20:01.258 --> 20:07.288
Obviously, one of the amazing things that all of Concord did this weekend and is doing this weekend is serve.

20:08.289 --> 20:11.114
This serve weekend is compassion in action.

20:11.495 --> 20:12.616
And it's awesome.

20:13.398 --> 20:16.242
I mean, as you go to schools and do the

20:16.450 --> 20:21.095
the work that is done there, whether it be some kind of service project, interacting with people.

20:21.576 --> 20:43.820
When you go to people's homes and do these cleanups and really minister to people there, when you go and serve food with firefighters and police officers and those in hospitals and those who first respond in other ways, you go even to trailheads and give food to people who are hungry that are hiking because, man, they're about to hike, they're going to be hungry or they get off the trail, they're hungry.

20:44.841 --> 20:45.842
But think about this.

20:47.106 --> 20:51.091
We don't minister to the lawn mower, right?

20:51.372 --> 20:52.573
We're cutting somebody's grass.

20:52.593 --> 20:53.915
We're not minister to the lawn mower.

20:54.476 --> 20:57.920
The lawn mower is a tool to minister to a person.

20:58.861 --> 21:13.320
And so my challenge to you is your compassion, will you take the time to use whatever gifts and resources, not just once a year, but every day to say, God, use me.

21:13.941 --> 21:14.962
I'm not going to wait.

21:15.554 --> 21:19.298
Until next year to serve again, I want to do it every single day.

21:19.798 --> 21:20.539
Think about Jesus.

21:21.039 --> 21:23.362
Did he only serve people once a year?

21:23.402 --> 21:28.827
Oh, everywhere he went, every day, he was on mission, everywhere.

21:31.950 --> 21:37.956
Not too long ago, I was in, on the other side of the world, in Myanmar, or Burma.

21:38.036 --> 21:39.678
Some people know it as Burma, Myanmar today.

21:40.699 --> 21:43.762
And I was with some friends there who were doing ministry in that country.

21:44.226 --> 21:49.254
And we were going with some locals, and we were going to a new neighborhood they were developing.

21:49.274 --> 21:55.122
Now these neighborhoods were pole-built, thatched roof, huts.

21:55.964 --> 22:01.752
And they were just, you know, made of bamboo poles, and they were for a person my size.

22:01.792 --> 22:03.855
The people in Myanmar are a little smaller than me.

22:04.096 --> 22:11.467
For a person my size, it was like a little bit scary to actually get up into the house because I was afraid the thing was gonna fall.

22:12.088 --> 22:13.650
But it didn't, it was well-built.

22:14.242 --> 22:18.487
But we were going, the people in Myanmar, for the most part, are Buddhist.

22:19.628 --> 22:35.526
As a matter of fact, when we were there, they were having one of their national holidays, and it was estimated that a million people went to this one Buddhist temple on the day we were there, a million people in and out, crazy.

22:36.727 --> 22:41.512
It's a hopeless religion, but this is what the people are, worshiping in that way.

22:42.073 --> 22:43.154
So we were going,

22:43.426 --> 22:44.207
hut to hut.

22:44.788 --> 22:53.480
And we were bringing with us five gallon pales that some of our friends have gotten some engineers and scientists together.

22:53.721 --> 23:00.090
They take five gallon pales and they take a clay pot link line with zinc.

23:01.071 --> 23:08.802
And this clay pot line with zinc actually takes, you can put any water in it and it will fill to the water and will become drinking water.

23:09.804 --> 23:11.506
And so we were taking these

23:11.810 --> 23:14.094
which were very valuable to the people there, right?

23:14.434 --> 23:28.496
And taking one per family and just going hut to hut and explaining why we were there, the translator would explain how to use the five gallon pail and this how it worked together and see if there any questions.

23:28.797 --> 23:34.366
And then he would turn and say, and here's this guy from America who's going to tell you why he is here.

23:34.927 --> 23:37.150
And that was my intro to explain the gospel.

23:37.491 --> 23:39.634
And I would talk about how the God of the universe

23:40.226 --> 23:54.926
He sent his son, Jesus, born of a virgin, lived a perfect life, died for us on the cross and rose again as a conquering King and Lord and draws people to salvation to everyone who will believe.

23:54.986 --> 23:58.390
And we would go house to house and talk about Jesus.

23:59.452 --> 24:02.175
And house to house when we would say, are you interested?

24:02.496 --> 24:03.858
They would say, not interested.

24:05.019 --> 24:07.122
And it was sad and we were sort of, oh,

24:07.298 --> 24:08.760
We were dejected, right?

24:08.820 --> 24:10.602
Because they kept saying no to Jesus.

24:11.543 --> 24:12.665
But we got to this one house.

24:14.727 --> 24:19.293
And at the end, as I shared, the translator looks at me and says, they're ready to believe.

24:20.714 --> 24:23.217
I said, did they understand the question?

24:23.778 --> 24:26.461
I mean, I was really, I have been said no to so many times.

24:26.501 --> 24:28.744
I said, did they understand what you asked them, what I asked them?

24:29.084 --> 24:30.086
He says, yes, they're ready.

24:30.626 --> 24:31.668
I said, are you sure?

24:31.708 --> 24:33.650
And he said, yes.

24:34.274 --> 24:35.195
I asked him one more time.

24:35.255 --> 24:37.097
I said, so they're ready to pray.

24:37.218 --> 24:38.279
I got really specific.

24:38.319 --> 24:40.001
They're ready to pray right now.

24:40.582 --> 24:41.303
And he said, yes.

24:41.943 --> 24:42.904
And we bowed our heads.

24:42.965 --> 24:44.787
And only God knows what they did in their hearts.

24:45.147 --> 24:46.108
Well, he did in their hearts.

24:46.669 --> 24:50.354
But man, they prayed to receive Jesus as Lord and Savior.

24:50.874 --> 25:03.890
Now the evidence that true salvation came was weeks later, we got an email from our ministry partners over there and they said, those people you guys went to visit, they're having a Bible study in their home now.

25:04.194 --> 25:05.476
is becoming a new church.

25:06.357 --> 25:12.246
So praise God their lives will change forever because of compassion and action.

25:13.628 --> 25:17.994
So you never know when a simple invite to somebody to come to church will change their life.

25:18.375 --> 25:22.902
You never know when spending time with someone over a cup of coffee is gonna minister to them.

25:23.422 --> 25:31.314
So I would encourage you to say God, how are you leading me to show compassion

25:31.394 --> 25:31.935
to others.

25:32.635 --> 25:37.480
My question to you is this, how is God leading you to show compassion to others?

25:38.120 --> 25:40.543
Not just once a year, but every day.

25:40.563 --> 25:45.387
And it may be different today and different tomorrow, but say, God, use me.

25:46.128 --> 25:50.132
Give me the kind of compassion Jesus had to minister to people in that way.

25:50.412 --> 25:56.658
When you do, God will use you to change someone's life forever as you connect them to Jesus.

25:57.278 --> 26:01.362
We continue to see and say, God, help me to see the crowds

26:01.570 --> 26:02.711
Help me to feel the compassion.

26:02.731 --> 26:03.512
Third thing is this.

26:03.953 --> 26:06.075
I want us to hear the call.

26:07.076 --> 26:08.157
I want us to hear the call.

26:08.518 --> 26:11.060
Verse 37, this is the call that Jesus gave.

26:11.861 --> 26:16.226
He says, then he said to his disciples and he says it to us.

26:16.947 --> 26:22.133
The harvest is abundant or plentiful, but the workers are few.

26:23.274 --> 26:24.956
Therefore, here's the call.

26:25.336 --> 26:30.642
Pray to the Lord of the harvest to send out workers into his harvest.

26:31.362 --> 26:32.643
It's a call in three ways.

26:32.723 --> 26:34.005
Number one, it's a call to pray.

26:34.766 --> 26:35.927
It is a call to pray.

26:37.008 --> 26:41.994
It's a call to pray for each one of us to say, God, there are lost people all around us.

26:42.855 --> 26:44.376
Send people to them.

26:45.618 --> 26:56.910
God may lay someone on your heart, somebody else from Concord, somebody else, even as a friend of yours or a family member, it's another believer that lives all the way across the world, across the country, across the state.

26:57.671 --> 26:58.532
And you pray for them.

26:59.172 --> 27:00.594
Maybe I encourage you,

27:00.738 --> 27:02.721
If God leads you to pray for them, hey, maybe do this.

27:04.504 --> 27:08.891
Write them a note, send them an email, send them a text and say, hey, man, you were on my heart.

27:09.432 --> 27:10.654
God led me to pray for you today.

27:10.854 --> 27:12.496
I pray that you'll be a witness for Christ today.

27:13.418 --> 27:15.581
So pray for them and let them know that.

27:16.242 --> 27:17.504
Man, it will be a blessing to them.

27:17.765 --> 27:28.882
But I'm begging you in your prayer time to pray that God would send out workers into His harvest field around the world and in our communities.

27:29.122 --> 27:30.403
that God would send out workers.

27:30.423 --> 27:31.524
So it's a call to pray.

27:31.985 --> 27:35.768
So maybe you're faithfully committed to that, and if you are, continue.

27:36.149 --> 27:41.674
But maybe you've never thought about how, you've never thought about how your prayers can impact eternity.

27:42.035 --> 27:43.256
Your prayers matter.

27:43.936 --> 27:44.757
It's a call to pray.

27:44.837 --> 27:48.521
Jesus says, ask the Lord of the harvest to send out workers into his harvest.

27:48.761 --> 27:51.003
So we're praying, God send them out.

27:51.023 --> 27:52.305
Number two, it's a call to give.

27:52.505 --> 27:57.970
If we are going to send them out, then some of them are going out as missionaries,

27:58.434 --> 28:00.316
And we send them out financially.

28:00.937 --> 28:10.890
And so I want to say, man, praise God for this church and our generous giving through the cooperative program, we support missionaries all around the world.

28:11.991 --> 28:16.857
And so whether you give a little bit or a lot as God leads you to give, we support missions.

28:17.438 --> 28:20.562
But we also support ministry and mission in our own community.

28:20.898 --> 28:23.642
And so Concord uses these resources as a church.

28:24.022 --> 28:26.926
We use these resources to impact the community.

28:26.946 --> 28:30.811
So it's a continued call to give, to send out workers.

28:31.612 --> 28:33.675
But it's also a call to go.

28:33.695 --> 28:35.898
It's a call to go.

28:36.539 --> 28:44.369
He says, therefore pray that the Lord of the harvest will send out workers into the harvest field.

28:45.010 --> 28:45.811
And I want to show you this.

28:47.013 --> 28:50.738
At the end of chapter nine, it's sort of like you got a group of guys there.

28:50.850 --> 28:52.872
They're huddled up like a football huddle.

28:54.233 --> 28:57.016
And they're huddled up, and Jesus says, all right, come here, boys, let's pray.

28:57.997 --> 29:04.683
And they're praying, and they're praying, and he's saying, I want you to pray that God would send out workers into the harvest fields.

29:05.484 --> 29:06.985
I'm praying, God send out workers.

29:07.346 --> 29:09.227
God send them out, send them out.

29:09.748 --> 29:11.770
And then at the end of chapter 9, it's like ready, break.

29:13.411 --> 29:14.552
And then you get to chapter 10.

29:16.574 --> 29:20.498
And Jesus calls them together and says, hey, boys, I'm sending you out.

29:23.138 --> 29:24.139
Here's what we see in that.

29:24.960 --> 29:28.084
Sometimes you're the answer to your very own prayer.

29:30.487 --> 29:31.668
God, send out a missionary.

29:33.210 --> 29:34.071
Maybe it's gonna be you.

29:35.493 --> 29:42.121
I've got a friend named Dwayne who, from North Dakota, he led a business for decades, retired from his business.

29:43.763 --> 29:52.594
God blessed him so he was able to retire even in his 50s, and he spent the next 20 years as a missionary in Southeast Asia.

29:54.402 --> 29:55.623
You may think I'm too old.

29:56.184 --> 29:57.165
You may think I'm too young.

29:58.507 --> 30:00.690
It's a call for all of us to go.

30:01.430 --> 30:03.253
It's a call for all of us to go.

30:03.613 --> 30:18.671
I saw a young boy about, he was in middle school, who taught a young boy about this big, who was from Zimbabwe, how to use a little evangel cube to explain the gospel.

30:19.732 --> 30:21.074
The boy from Zimbabwe

30:22.274 --> 30:24.758
Saw a guy who was from Nepal.

30:25.359 --> 30:26.500
This is true story.

30:26.561 --> 30:28.664
This was in Clarkson, Georgia, not too long ago.

30:29.104 --> 30:41.303
So a kid from America teaches a boy from Zimbabwe who shows a guy from Nepal, these pictures, and the guy from Nepal right there says, I want to receive Jesus.

30:42.685 --> 30:43.506
You never know.

30:43.546 --> 30:46.070
It's a call for all of us to go.

30:46.531 --> 30:49.275
And so my question to you is, how will you respond today?

30:50.056 --> 30:51.218
Will you say, God?

30:52.130 --> 30:54.573
I will pray like never before.

30:56.396 --> 30:59.880
God, I want to see through your eyes.

31:00.481 --> 31:03.705
I want to see the crowds the way you see them.

31:03.725 --> 31:05.367
I want to feel the compassion.

31:05.728 --> 31:08.912
So today maybe you're just call God.

31:08.932 --> 31:10.534
I want to be like Jesus in those ways.

31:11.655 --> 31:13.277
For some of you, it may be a call to go.

31:13.297 --> 31:16.481
I mean, you may have never thought about it before.

31:17.283 --> 31:19.986
You may need to respond today and say, I don't know what this looks like,

31:20.130 --> 31:26.297
Man, maybe I'm gonna be going out into the community, or I'm willing, if God's called me to go to the nations, I'll go to the nations.

31:28.299 --> 31:31.262
Some of you may need to respond today with salvation.

31:31.703 --> 31:39.772
Maybe you need to even come and become a member of this church, or even to say I wanna respond to Jesus' obedience through baptism.

31:40.152 --> 31:45.538
So I wanna lead us in a word of prayer, and today I wanna ask you to respond the way God's letting you respond.

31:45.558 --> 31:46.259
Let's pray together.

31:47.000 --> 31:49.202
Heavenly Father, we love you.

31:50.178 --> 31:53.523
And as we look at your word, we see Jesus.

31:55.205 --> 32:01.455
And Lord, for those of us who know you as Lord and Savior, we have been saved by your grace.

32:02.136 --> 32:10.047
We've been given your love and forgiveness, and you compel us, Lord, to be on mission everywhere.

32:11.229 --> 32:14.614
And so God, only you know what you're doing in the hearts and lives of the people in this room.

32:15.195 --> 32:17.298
But I pray that each of us would respond

32:17.858 --> 32:19.620
that we would see people the way you see them.

32:19.720 --> 32:25.286
We would feel your compassion as we see the crowds and feel the compassion and we would hear your call.

32:26.367 --> 32:30.111
And God, maybe it's a call for us to pray that you would use us this week.

32:30.832 --> 32:32.514
It's a call to give, it's a call to go.

32:34.236 --> 32:39.161
Father, again, maybe there's other ways that we need to respond by becoming a member of this church.

32:40.883 --> 32:43.986
Father, by even responding through

32:44.098 --> 32:47.823
saying at some point in the future, I wanna be obedient to Jesus through baptism.

32:48.684 --> 32:52.770
And so Father, I pray that each one of us would respond the way of your leading us to respond.

32:54.453 --> 33:00.481
But now here in this room, I have a specific question for you before we sing, before I pray one more time.

33:01.122 --> 33:04.367
Do you know Jesus as your Lord and savior?

33:05.568 --> 33:12.498
If you say I don't yet know him as Lord and savior, then in just a moment, I'm gonna ask you to stand when we all stand

33:13.122 --> 33:20.253
And I ask you to come to me or Brandon, one of the other leaders here at the front and just say, today I want to give my life to Christ.

33:21.596 --> 33:25.582
Again, maybe you've given your life to Christ recently and you say, I want to be baptized.

33:25.862 --> 33:28.887
We would love and celebrate with you and we'll get that set up soon.

33:29.228 --> 33:32.213
Or maybe others who say, I want to become a member of this church.

33:32.713 --> 33:34.877
This is the church where I want to serve the world.

33:34.917 --> 33:37.862
I see what this church is all about and I'm all about that too.

33:38.503 --> 33:40.626
And you want to come, so today,

33:41.090 --> 33:43.434
I'm asking you to respond the way you need to respond.

33:43.474 --> 33:53.890
Maybe others simply want to come and pray here at the front and just say, I want to continue to pray for our community and pray for Concord that God would use us as a church to be all he wants us to be.

33:54.831 --> 33:57.135
Let me pray and we'll stand and we'll sing and you come.

33:57.235 --> 34:03.605
Lord Jesus, we ask that you have your way now to this time of response, that each one of us would respond the way you're leading us to do that.

34:04.427 --> 34:07.251
And we love you and Jesus and we pray, amen.

34:07.652 --> 34:09.234
As we stand and sing, you come.

